   <taskbody>
      <context class="- topic/section task/context ">
         <p class="- topic/p ">Follow this procedure to reset the batch system after an E-Stop (emergency stop) or fault:</p>
      </context>
      <steps class="- topic/ol task/steps ">
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">If an <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">E-Stop</uicontrol> button or cable is activated:</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">The integration panel alarm sounds.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Determine why the E-stop was activated.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Verify that no personnel were injured. Make sure that all personnel and
                     materials are safely out of the way before reactivating.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">To reset the<uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol "> E-stop</uicontrol> button, turn the button according
                     to the arrows molded on the button.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">To reset an E-stop cable, turn the handle until the indicator points to
                     “I”.</li>
               </ul>
               <p class="- topic/p ">
                  <fig id="fig_npv_g3y_rcc" class="- topic/fig ">
                     <image href="media/image2.jpg"
                            placement="break"
                            id="image_s55_hjy_rcc"
                            align="center"
                            class="- topic/image "/>
                  </fig>
               </p>
            </info>
         </step>
         <step class="- topic/li task/step ">
            <cmd class="- topic/ph task/cmd ">Turn the E-Stop reset key switches on the integration panel.</cmd>
            <info class="- topic/itemgroup task/info ">
               <ul class="- topic/ul ">
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Do not turn the “MGUARD” key switch.</li>
                  <li class="- topic/li ">Then press the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">blue System Restart</uicontrol> button on the right
                     of the <uicontrol class="+ topic/ph ui-d/uicontrol ">E-Stop</uicontrol> button.</li>
               </ul>
               <note type="note" id="note_xjf_kjy_rcc" class="- topic/note ">
                  <p class="- topic/p ">To restart the cullet system, refer to BAT-ET-102B Cullet System: Reset After
                     an E-Stop.</p>
               </note>
